<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,1117,1358]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
The following 
<collectingCountry box="[317,429,1117,1142]" name="Argentina" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Argentina</collectingCountry>
records of 36 species in eight genera will most certainly be markedly increased by further collecting.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,1117,1358]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
Formerly a subfamily in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schilling" authorityYear="1829" box="[531,646,1189,1214]" class="Insecta" family="Lygaeidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Lygaeidae</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Slater" box="[711,872,1189,1214]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" refString="Slater, J. A. (1964) A catalogue of the Lygaeidae of the World. Vol. 1 &amp; 2. University of Connecticut, Storrs, 1668 pp. [pp. i - xviii + 1 - 778 &amp; pp. 779 - 1668.]" type="book chapter" year="1964">J. Slater 1964</bibRefCitation>
, 435 and J. Slater and O’Donnell 1995, 44), this group was elevated to family status by 
<bibRefCitation author="Henry" box="[589,812,1225,1250]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" refString="Henry, T. J. (1997 a) Phylogenetic analysis of family groups within the infraorder Pentatomomorpha (Hemiptera: Heteroptera), with emphasis on the Lygaeoidea. Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 90, 275 - 301. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / 90.3.275" type="journal article" year="1997" yearSuffix="a">Henry (1997a, 296)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,1117,1358]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<taxonomicName box="[199,293,1261,1286]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Amorgius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="major">
<collectingRegion box="[199,219,1262,1286]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">A</collectingRegion>
major
</taxonomicName>
monograph on the “Systematics, Phylogeny, and Zoogeography of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[1114,1217,1261,1286]" class="Insecta" family="Blissidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Blissinae">Blissinae</taxonomicName>
of the World” was published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Slater" box="[305,495,1297,1322]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" refString="Slater, J. A. (1979 a) Systematics, phylogeny, and zoogeography of the Blissinae of the World. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 165, 1 - 180." type="journal article" year="1979" yearSuffix="a">J. Slater (1979a)</bibRefCitation>
; it contains a key (pages 58–61) to 46 genera and a checklist of all known species and keys to most of them.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
